    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UIPanGestureRecognizer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is a concrete subclass of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uigesturerecognizer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Clients of this class can, in their action methods, query the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UIPanGestureRecognizer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object for the current translation of the gesture ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uipangesturerecognizer/1621207-translationinview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") and the velocity of the translation ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uipangesturerecognizer/1621209-velocityinview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "). They can specify a view’s coordinate system to use for the translation and velocity values. Clients can also reset the translation to a desired value."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The user must press one or more fingers on a view while panning it. A panning gesture is continuous. It begins ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uigesturerecognizerstate/uigesturerecognizerstatebegan"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") when the user moves the minimum number of fingers allowed ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uipangesturerecognizer/1621210-minimumnumberoftouches"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") enough distance for recognition as a pan. It changes ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uigesturerecognizerstate/uigesturerecognizerstatechanged"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") when the user moves a finger while pressing with the minimum number of fingers. It ends ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uigesturerecognizerstate/uigesturerecognizerstateended"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") when the user lifts all fingers."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
